      "last_qa_date": "2026-06-06",
      "description": "Vought F4U-1A Corsair (Bureau #49668), ditched April 17, 1945 by 2nd Lt. William H. Holden after engine failure on transit from Molokai to Ewa Airfield (some sources say 1946—date contested). Aircraft: 33 ft 4 in long, 41 ft wingspan. Sits upright at ~110-115 ft in Maunalua Bay off Hawaii Kai. No penetration permitted. Garden eels, frogfish, leaf scorpionfish, moray eels."
    }
